text.tspan: Barry is our resident urban legend. If you look out
behind the mansion, you'll see a giant field of grass,
wheat, or corn, depending on the season. Right now
it's wheat and corn. In the middle of the field is a your
average sentient, living, breathing, walking scarecrow.
But according to the legend, every so often he'll take
somebody from the mansion into a maze that he makes
in the field overnight, and forces them to go all the
way through it. It's not like he's going to take their
soul or something if they fail; he isn't evil in any way.
He just really likes his corn mazes, and wants to get
better at making them. He spends most of his time in
the field, just sitting there and doing nothing, but
sometimes he'll hang out with me, Filum (we'll get to
him later), and Bethany in the mansion. He and
Bethany are actually really close.
Barry
He's Barry scary (get it?!)
Age: He's a scarecrow they don't age
Species: Scarecrow
Alignment: Chaotic
That one time I told him
a joke (it wasn't funny)
